##########################################\n## VOCABOLARY & EXPRESSIONS\n##################################################\n\n? Choose the correct synonym for “important”:\n- [x] Significant\n- [ ] Tiny\n- [ ] Useless\n\n? Choose the correct meaning of “to attend a meeting”:\n- [x] To be present at a meeting\n- [ ] To organize a meeting\n- [ ] To cancel a meeting\n\n? The opposite of “increase” is:\n- [x] Decrease\n- [ ] Grow\n- [ ] Improve\n\n? “Deadline” refers to:\n- [x] A date by which something must be done\n- [ ] Start of a project\n- [ ] Optional task\n\n? “Feedback” in a work context means:\n- [x] Comments on performance or work done\n- [ ] A bonus\n- [ ] Absence notice\n\n? “Schedule” is:\n- [x] A plan of activities or events\n- [ ] A person’s salary\n- [ ] A type of contract\n\n? “Requirement” means:\n- [x] Something needed for a task\n- [ ] Optional suggestion\n- [ ] Deadline\n\n? “Guideline” refers to:\n- [x] Recommended way to do something\n- [ ] Mandatory rule\n- [ ] Random choice\n\n##################################################\n## GRAMMAR: VERBS & TENSES\n##################################################\n\n? Choose the correct form: “She ___ to work every day.”\n- [x] goes\n- [ ] go\n- [ ] gone\n\n? “I have worked here since 2015.” indicates:\n- [x] Action started in past and continues now\n- [ ] Completed action in past\n- [ ] Future action\n\n? “He ___ already finished the report.” Choose the correct tense.\n- [x] has\n- [ ] had\n- [ ] will\n\n? Passive form of “They will complete the project” is:\n- [x] The project will be completed by them\n- [ ] The project is completed by them\n- [ ] The project complete by them\n\n? Correct conditional: “If I ___ more time, I would help you.”\n- [x] had\n- [ ] have\n- [ ] will have\n\n? Choose correct past simple: “Yesterday she ___ to the office.”\n- [x] went\n- [ ] go\n- [ ] gone\n\n? Present continuous of “He reads a book” is:\n- [x] He is reading a book\n- [ ] He reads a book\n- [ ] He reading a book\n\n? Future tense: “We ___ start the meeting at 10.”\n- [x] will\n- [ ] are\n- [ ] have\n\n##################################################\n## GRAMMAR: PREPOSITIONS & CONNECTORS\n##################################################\n\n? Choose correct preposition: “I am interested ___ digital technologies.”\n- [x] in\n- [ ] on\n- [ ] at\n\n? Choose correct preposition: “She is responsible ___ the project.”\n- [x] for\n- [ ] of\n- [ ] about\n\n? Connectors: “I studied hard, ___ I failed the exam.”\n- [x] but\n- [ ] so\n- [ ] because\n\n? Fill in: “He is working late ___ finish the report.”\n- [x] to\n- [ ] for\n- [ ] at\n\n? Correct: “I will call you ___ I arrive.”\n- [x] when\n- [ ] while\n- [ ] although\n\n? Choose correct: “She stayed at home ___ it was raining.”\n- [x] because\n- [ ] but\n- [ ] so\n\n? Fill in: “They left early ___ avoid traffic.”\n- [x] to\n- [ ] for\n- [ ] at\n\n? Connector: “He didn’t attend the meeting ___ he was sick.”\n- [x] because\n- [ ] but\n- [ ] so\n\n##################################################\n## READING & UNDERSTANDING\n##################################################\n\n? What does “The company is expanding its services abroad” mean?\n- [x] The company is increasing its activities in other countries\n- [ ] The company is reducing services\n- [ ] The company is closing branches\n\n? “Employees must comply with safety regulations” means:\n- [x] Workers must follow safety rules\n- [ ] Workers can ignore safety rules\n- [ ] Safety rules are optional\n\n? “The project deadline is approaching” indicates:\n- [x] The due date is near\n- [ ] The project has no due date\n- [ ] The project is cancelled\n\n? “Please find attached the report” means:\n- [x] The report is included with the message\n- [ ] The report is missing\n- [ ] The report is verbal\n\n? “He is on leave this week” means:\n- [x] He is absent from work temporarily\n- [ ] He is fired\n- [ ] He is traveling abroad for business\n\n? “The new policy will come into effect next month” means:\n- [x] The policy starts next month\n- [ ] The policy is cancelled\n- [ ] The policy is optional\n\n? “The meeting has been postponed” means:\n- [x] The meeting was delayed\n- [ ] The meeting is cancelled permanently\n- [ ] The meeting will be earlier\n\n? “She is in charge of the project” means:\n- [x] She is responsible for it\n- [ ] She is attending it\n- [ ] She is observing\n\n##################################################\n## WRITING & COMMUNICATION\n##################################################\n\n? Choose correct sentence:\n- [x] I have completed the task on time\n- [ ] I completed task on timeed\n- [ ] I has complete the task\n\n? Choose correct: “We need to discuss the budget before finalizing it.”\n- [x] Correct\n- [ ] Incorrect\n- [ ] Partially correct\n\n? Email formal closing: “Yours faithfully” is used when:\n- [x] Recipient name is unknown\n- [ ] Recipient name is known\n- [ ] Only informal emails\n\n? Email formal closing: “Best regards” is used when:\n- [x] Informal or semi-formal emails\n- [ ] Only formal official letters\n- [ ] Only personal letters\n\n? Choose correct plural: “One analysis, two ___”\n- [x] analyses\n- [ ] analysises\n- [ ] analysi\n\n? Correct comparative: “This report is ___ than the previous one.”\n- [x] more detailed\n- [ ] detailer\n- [ ] detailedest\n\n? Fill in: “Please ___ the form before sending.”\n- [x] complete\n- [ ] completes\n- [ ] completing\n\n? Choose correct preposition: “He is responsible ___ managing the team.”\n- [x] for\n- [ ] of\n- [ ] about\n:::\n','2026-02-17 09:57:28','2026-02-17 09:57:52',114,'quiz',0),(140,'Actions','Le *Actions* sono funzioni server che puoi definire e chiamare dal client, con validazione automatica dei dati e gestione degli errori **type-safe**\n\n\n## Lato Backend\n1. Definire le Actions (nel backend)\nCrei un file src/actions/ (o simile) con le tue azioni:\n```javascript\n// src/actions/index.ts\nimport { defineAction, z } from \"astro:actions\";\n\nexport const server = {\n  // Azione per salvare una nota\n  saveNote: defineAction({\n    input: z.object({\n      title: z.string(),\n      content: z.string(),\n      id: z.string().optional(),\n    }),\n    handler: async (input) => {\n      // Logica server (accesso DB, operazioni sicure)\n      const result = await db.notes.save(input);\n      return result;\n    },\n  }),\n\n  // Azione per eliminare una nota\n  deleteNote: defineAction({\n    input: z.string(), // ID della nota\n    handler: async (noteId) => {\n      await db.notes.delete(noteId);\n      return { success: true };\n    },\n  }),\n};\n```\n\n## Lato Frontend\n2. Usare nel client\n```javascript\n<!-- Componente.svelte -->\n<script>\n  import { actions } from \"astro:actions\";\n\n  async function handleSave() {\n    // Type-safe! L\'IDE sa che input deve avere title, content, id\n    const result = await actions.saveNote({\n      title: \"Mia Nota\",\n      content: \"Contenuto...\",\n      id: \"nota-123\"\n    });\n    \n    if (result.error) {\n      console.error(result.error);\n    } else {\n      console.log(\"Salvata:\", result.data);\n    }\n  }\n</script>\n\n<button on:click={handleSave}>Salva Nota</button>\n```\n','2026-02-19 15:17:13','2026-02-23 11:51:43',7,'note',0),(141,'Nota [75] - 19/02/2026',':::slide Presentazione di Esempio\n![Immagine 1](/WebApp/image1.png)\n---\n```javascript\nconst hello = \"Hello World\";\nconsole.log(hello);\n```\n---\n![Immagine 2](/WebApp/image2.png)\n:::','2026-02-19 15:19:57','2026-02-23 13:28:24',53,'slide',1),(142,'Nota [76] - 19/02/2026',':::quiz Esame di Storia Digitale\n::time 2min\n::ok 1\n::error -0.5\n::null 0\n\n? Qual è il componente principale di questa applicazione?\n- [ ] React\n- [x] Astro + Svelte\n- [ ] Vue.js\n\n? Come si chiama lo stile grafico utilizzato?\n- [ ] Material Design\n- [ ] Glassmorphism\n- [x] Retro Typewriter\n:::','2026-02-19 15:20:33','2026-02-19 15:21:59',141,'quiz',0),(145,'Collections','Le *Content Collections* sono un sistema per organizzare e gestire contenuti strutturati (markdown, MDX, JSON, YAML) in modo type-safe.\nSi definiscono in **src/content/** e vengono validate tramite uno schema **Zod** definito in **src/content/config.ts.**\n\n### 1) src/content/config.ts\ndefinisci la collection e il suo schema:\n```javascript\nimport { defineCollection, z } from \'astro:content\';\n\nconst blog = defineCollection({\n  schema: z.object({\n    title: z.string(),\n    date: z.date(),\n    draft: z.boolean().optional(),\n  }),\n});\n\nexport const collections = { blog };\n```\n\n### 2) src/content/blog/primo-post.md\nun contenuto della collection:\n```markdown\n---\ntitle: \"Il mio primo post\"\ndate: 2024-01-15\ndraft: false\n---\n\nContenuto del post...\n```\n### 3) src/content/blog/primo-post.md\nsrc/pages/blog.astro\n```html\n---\nimport { getCollection } from \'astro:content\';\n\nconst posts = await getCollection(\'blog\');\n// opzionale: filtra i draft\n// const posts = await getCollection(\'blog\', ({ data }) => !data.draft);\n---\n\n<ul>\n  {posts.map(post => (\n    <li>\n      <a href={`/blog/${post.slug}`}>{post.data.title}</a>\n    </li>\n  ))}\n</ul>\n```\n','2026-02-20 13:36:34','2026-02-23 16:23:04',7,'note',0),(148,'Componente','Ogni componente contiene insieme:\n- HTML\n- CSS\n- JavaScript\n\ntutto nello stesso file.\n\n## Reattività automatica\n\nIn Svelte non serve usare **hook** o *state manager complessi*.\nSe cambi una variabile → l’interfaccia si aggiorna automaticamente.\n\n\n```html\n\n<script>\n  let count = 0; // count è reattivo automaticamente \n\n  $: doubled = count * 2; //$: significa: “ricalcola quando cambia una dipendenza”\n\n  function increment() {\n    count += 1; // (Svelte aggiorna il DOM)\n  }\n</script>\n\n<style>\n  button {\n    font-size: 20px;\n    padding: 10px;\n  }\n</style>\n\n<!-- binding -->\n<!-- Le {} inseriscono variabili JS direttamente nel markup. -->\n<h1>Contatore: {count}  → {doubled} </h1>\n\n<button on:click={increment}> \n  Aumenta\n</button>\n\n\n```\n','2026-02-23 13:02:43','2026-02-23 13:23:34',12,'note',0),(149,'Svelte 5','\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th> </th>\n      <th> Svelte 4 </th>\n      <th> Svelte 5 </th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr> <td>Reattività</td> <td>implicita</td> <td>runes esplicite</td> </tr>\n    <tr> <td>Stato</td> <td>variabili</td> <td><code>$state()</code></td> </tr>\n    <tr> <td>Derived</td> <td><code>$:</code></td> <td><code>$derived()</code></td> </tr>\n    <tr> <td>Effetti</td> <td><code>$:</code></td> <td><code>$effect()</code></td> </tr>\n    <tr> <td>Granularità</td> <td>per componente</td> <td>fine-grained</td> </tr>\n\n<tr> <td>Scalabilità</td> <td>buona</td> <td>molto migliore</td> </tr>\n    \n  </tbody>\n</table>','2026-02-23 13:24:28','2026-02-23 13:48:10',12,'note',1),(150,'Componente','```html\n\n<script>\n  let count = $state(0);\n\n  let doubled = $derived(count * 2);\n\n  function increment() {\n    count++;\n  }\n\n  $effect(() => {\n    console.log(\"Count changed:\", count);\n  });\n</script>\n\n<h1>{count}</h1>\n<p>Doppio: {doubled}</p>\n\n<button onclick={increment}>\n  +\n</button>\n```','2026-02-23 13:51:33','2026-02-24 15:12:04',149,'note',2),(151,'Runes','## $state - Stato reattivo\n\n```javascript\nlet count = $state(0);\n```\nQuando cambia la variabile dello stato viene aggiornata la UI\n\n## $derived - Valori derivati\n```html\n<script>\n  let count = $state(2);\n\n  let doubled = $derived(count * 2); // <--\n</script>\n\n<p>{count}</p>\n<p>Doppio: {doubled}</p>\n\n```\nla variabile si aggiorna quando cambia il valore della variabile da cui dipende \n\n## $effect - Effetti collaterali\n\nCodice che deve eseguire qualcosa quando cambia lo stato.\n```html\n<script>\n  let count = $state(0);\n\n  $effect(() => {\n    console.log(\"Nuovo valore:\", count);\n  });\n</script>\n```\n\n##  $props - Props del componente\n\nRicevere dati da un componente padre.\n\n#### Child.svelte\n```html\n<script>\n  let { name } = $props();\n</script>\n\n<h2>Ciao {name}</h2>\n```\n\n#### Parent.svelte\n```html\n<Child name=\"Luca\" /></script>\n```\n##  $props - callback \n\n Si utilizza le $props anche per passare i dati dal figlio al padre tramite **callback**.\n\n#### Parent.svelte\n```html\n\n<script>\n  import Child from \"./Child.svelte\";\n\n  let message = $state(\"Nessun dato\");\n\n  function handleMessage(value) {\n    message = value;\n  }\n</script>\n\n<h2>Messaggio dal figlio:</h2>\n<p>{message}</p>\n\n<Child onSend={handleMessage} />\n```\n\n#### Cild.svelte\n```html\n<script>\n  let { onSend } = $props();\n\n  function sendData() {\n    onSend(\"Ciao dal figlio \");\n  }\n</script>\n\n<button onclick={sendData}>\n  Invia al padre\n</button>\n```\n\n\n## debug\n\nPer vedere cosa succede nello stato.\n```javascript\n$inspect(count);\n```','2026-02-23 14:02:28','2026-02-24 15:06:49',149,'note',1);
